Well, so, that's how I flew today.
First point of criticism: We need more attractive logbooks. Black is boring, pink is not really pink, but more like salmon color.
I wanted to fly since I was little.
And today it was so... Today I flew an airplane. I haven't quite processed that yet.
Data from Flightaware.
I try to go there again next Saturday. The weather doesn't look so good right now, but it's also only Monday.
It is already becoming clear where the problems lie. It will probably be VERY difficult to get the medical permission, due to the FAA's opinion on certain medications.
It is not impossible, but it will TAKE VERY long and means A LOT of extra work.
That is somewhat discouraging, but nevertheless just another problem that you have to solve. So far, it seems solvable. It only costs a lot of time and money.
If you want to know what awaits me.
The FAA is not a fan of ADHD. They definitely won't let you get a medical certificate if you're taking medication for it.
