Also, I found a pink logbook.
Happy Saturday morning. This is what I did today ^_^
#TeaganAir
It's officially in the logbook. I have 2.3 flight hours ^_^
#TeaganAir
If I had to describe what it's like to fly in a small aircraft, I would say it's like a mixture of a motorcycle/quad and a boat 4,000 feet in the air.
On the ground you are immediately very fast. Everything is a bit unstable on the ground, hence motorcycle/quad.
And if you didn't know yet: You steer an airplane on the ground with your feet, not with the control yoke. Rudder pedals and brakes. It's not a car.
In the air it's wobbly and you kind of swim. It feels as if you were in a boat on water. You can steer it, but sometimes a wave comes and throws you a little off course, so you have to get used to the motion of the sea, just in the air.
Another random detail:
Flying is physically demanding. My back and legs *hurt* today, as if I had been at the gym.
This is not like a Sunday drive in a car. It's more of a sport than a leisurely drive, in my new opinion.
A nice Saturday, my loves. Welcome to 4.000 feet.
Tomorrow I'll go there again. Then we'll practice flow and slow flying.
Today the weather was turbulent, but it was a lot of fun. We practiced slow flying and flow. Once we had a ground speed of only 16 mph at a airspeed of 65.
It was a nice clear day, a bit foggy up above, but still nice.
